AB  - Hercowitz (1986) estimates aggregate output and hours equations which are derived from a new classical model of aggregate supply. Under an alternative interpretation, his aggregate supply equation is in fact an IS curve with one omitted variable, while his hours equation is best interpreted as an Okun's Law relationship. When the Hercowitz equations are nested in more general formulations which incorporate these alternatives, the new classical restrictions are rejected resoundingly.
